克拉克大學是一所規模較小的大學，有30多個本科學位。其學科以地理和心理學見長。此外該大學對有B+以上成績的本科生提供免費的第五年研究生教育。<ref name=07catalog>{{cite book |editor-last=Griffin-Kumpey |editor-first=Tammy |title=Clark University Academic Catalog 2007–2008 |publisher=Clark University Communications Office |location=Worcester |date=June 1, 2007 |page=5 |accessdate=2014-09-18}}</ref> 录取率在50%左右<ref name=CDS2014>{{cite web |url=https://www2.clarku.edu/aboutclark/pdfs/CDS_2014_2015_Clarku.pdf |title=Common Data Set 2014-2015 |publisher=Clark University |accessdate=2018-10-09 |archive-date=2015-09-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150905230512/http://www.clarku.edu/aboutclark/pdfs/CDS_2014_2015_Clarku.pdf |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

该大学以理科见长，与[[伍斯特理工学院|伍斯特理工学院]]和[[圣十字学院|圣十字学院]]课程互通。它被评为[[改變人生的大學|改變人生的大學]]之一。<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.usnews.com/education/best-colleges/articles/2015/09/24/central-massachusetts-college-road-trip-clark-university|title=Central Massachusetts College Road Trip: Clark University|last=Gearon|first=Christopher J.|date=24 September 2015|website=U.S. News & World Report|publisher=U.S. News & World Report LP|accessdate=27 June 2016|archive-date=2016-08-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160815055427/http://www.usnews.com/education/best-colleges/articles/2015/09/24/central-massachusetts-college-road-trip-clark-university|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://colleges.usnews.rankingsandreviews.com/best-colleges/clark-university-massachusetts-2139 |title=U.S. News Best Colleges Rankings – Clark University |publisher=''U.S. News & World Report'' |accessdate=27 June 2016 |archive-date=2016-07-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160721025247/http://colleges.usnews.rankingsandreviews.com/best-colleges/clark-university-massachusetts-2139 |dead-url=no }}</ref>

==学生==
该大学的本科生主要来自麻省以外，国际学生大概占全体学生总数的15%。<ref name="ClarkFastFacts"/>
该大学要求大一大二学生住校，总共住校的本科生占全体学生数的70%。<ref name="ClarkCampusLifeQandA">[http://www.clarku.edu/undergraduate-admissions/campus-life/campus-life-questions.cfm "Campus Life Questions and Answers"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.clarku.edu/undergraduate-admissions/campus-life/campus-life-questions.cfm |date=20150512020042 }}, ''Clark University Office of Admissions''. Retrieved 23 May 2015.</ref>
